          "candidate_value": "Visit your nearest branch to get a stamp in Part C of the enrolment form.) Option 2.",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-d83760f7fc5500fb",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "2. Direct deposit of government payments\nYou can also set up Direct Deposit for recurring government payments such as monthly pension cheques.\nHere\u2019s how you can enrol:\nOption 1. Visit directdeposit.gc.ca and complete the enrolment form. To enrol you need:\nYour name, address and date of birth\nYour payment type(s) and the associated personal identifier(s), for example your Social Insurance Number (SIN) or your file number\nA void cheque or your bank account information (No void cheque? No problem! Visit your nearest branch to get a stamp in Part C of the enrolment form.)\nOption 2. You can also enrol in direct deposit on My CRA Account , My Service Canada Account or My VAC Account\nOption 3. Forms are also available at your local branch.\nGovernment of Canada information officers are available to help you at 1-800-593-1666, in English and in French, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Saturday",
          "source_document_id": "src-scotia-html-950b990f53b5c20e",
